<p>The <b>radian</b>, denoted by the symbol <b>rad</b>, is the unit of <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angle" title=3D"Angle">angle</a> in th=
e <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_System_of_Units" t=
itle=3D"International System of Units">International System of Units</a> (S=
I) and is the standard unit of angular measure used in many areas of <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics" title=3D"Mathematics">mathe=
matics</a>. It is defined such that one radian is the angle subtended at th=
e center of a plane circle by an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C=
ircular_arc" title=3D"Circular arc">arc</a> that is equal in length to the =
radius.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Radian#cite_note-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The unit is defined in the S=
I as the coherent unit for plane angle, as well as for phase angle.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Radian#cite_note-2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Angles without explicitly specified units =
are generally assumed to be measured in radians, especially in mathematical=
 writing.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Radian#cite_note-3"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<meta property=3D"mw:PageProp/toc">
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Definition">Definition</h2>=
</div>
<p>One radian is defined as the angle at the center of a circle in a plane =
that is <a href=3D"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/subtend" class=3D"extiw" =
title=3D"wikt:subtend">subtended</a> by an arc whose length equals the radi=
us of the circle.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radian#cite_note-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> More generally, th=
e <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnitude_(mathematics)" title=
=3D"Magnitude (mathematics)">magnitude</a> in radians of a subtended angle =
is equal to the ratio of the arc length to the radius of the circle; that i=
s, <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>=CE=B8</i> =3D <i>s</i>/<i>r</i></span>, wher=
e <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CE=B8</span> i=
s the magnitude in radians of the subtended angle, <span class=3D"texhtml m=
var" style=3D"font-style:italic;">s</span> is arc length, and <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">r</span> is radius. A <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Right_angle" title=3D"Right angle">right=
 angle</a> is exactly <span class=3D"texhtml">=CF=80/2</span> radians.<sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Radian#cite_note-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>One <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complete_revolution" cl=
ass=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Complete revolution">complete revolution</a>, =
expressed as an angle in radians, is the length of the circumference divide=
d by the radius, which is <span class=3D"texhtml">2<span class=3D"texhtml m=
var" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CF=80</span><i>r</i>/<i>r</i></span>, or=
 <span class=3D"texhtml">2<i>=CF=80</i></span>. Thus, <span class=3D"texhtm=
l">2<i>=CF=80</i></span>&nbsp;radians is equal to 360&nbsp;degrees. The rel=
ation <span class=3D"texhtml">2<i>=CF=80</i> rad =3D 360=C2=B0</span> can b=
e derived using the formula for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ar=
c_length" title=3D"Arc length">arc length</a>, <span class=3D"nowrap">=E2=
=81=A0<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><=
math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle=
