https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radian#cite_note-FOOTNOTEMohrShirleyPhillipsT=
rott20228%E2%80%939-27"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>26<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Current SI can be considered relative to this framework as a <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_unit" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Natural unit">natural unit</a> system where the equation <span class=3D=
"texhtml"><i>=CE=B7</i> =3D 1</span> is assumed to hold, or similarly, <spa=
n class=3D"nowrap">1 rad =3D 1</span>. This <i>radian convention</i> allows=
 the omission of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=
=CE=B7</span> in mathematical formulas.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEQuincey2=
021_28-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radi=
an#cite_note-FOOTNOTEQuincey2021-28"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2=
7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Defining radian as a base unit may be useful for software, where the=
 disadvantage of longer equations is minimal.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-29" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radian#cite_note-29=
"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>28<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup> For example, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boo=
st_(C%2B%2B_libraries)" title=3D"Boost (C++ libraries)">Boost</a> units lib=
rary defines angle units with a <code>plane_angle</code> dimension,<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-30" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Radian#cite_note-30"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>29<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Mathematica" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Mathematica">Mathematica=
</a>'s unit system similarly considers angles to have an angle dimension.<s=
up id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEMohrShirleyPhillipsTrott20223_31-0" class=3D"refe=
rence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radian#cite_note-FOOTNOTEMo=
hrShirleyPhillipsTrott20223-31"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>30<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-32" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radian#cite_note-32"><=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>31<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup>
</p>
